<item>
            <title>[HIVE-25794] CombineHiveRecordReader: log statements in a loop leads to memory pressure</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-25794</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-16150&quot; title=&quot;LLAP: HiveInputFormat:getRecordReader: Fix log statements to reduce memory pressure&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-16150&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-16150&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, a huge string will be built in a loop, even the log level is INFO. That leads to memory pressure when processing a big number of split files.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/master/ql/src/java/org/apache/hadoop/hive/ql/io/CombineHiveRecordReader.java#L116&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;CombineHiveRecordReader.java&lt;/a&gt;, the following needs to be fixed.&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;LOG.debug(&quot;Found spec for &quot; + path + &quot; &quot; + otherPart + &quot; from &quot; + pathToPartInfo);&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
